summary: Next-gen financial advisor Heather Robison teamed up with her mother to grow a $460 million business in Oklahoma using tax planning as a differentiator.

headline: Layoffs are piling up, raising worker anxiety. Here are some companies that have cut jobs recently
summary: It’s a tough time to be looking for a job.  Amid wider economic uncertainty, some analysts have said that businesses are at a “no-hire, no fire” standstill.  Others cite corporate restructuring more broadly — or, as seen with big names like Amazon, are redirecting money to artificial intelligence.

headline: Is ConocoPhillips Set for a Rebound After Its Latest Energy Sector Acquisitions?
summary: Ever wondered if now is the right time to dive into ConocoPhillips stock? Let’s break down what the numbers and recent events say about its true value. The share price has had a choppy ride lately. It slipped 1.2% in the last week, ticked up 1.1% over the past month, but is still down 12.1% for the year to date and 19.8% over the last twelve months.
